# Handoff prompts to a fresh agent

Keep them small — pointer + delta, not a transcript.

A fresh agent already has:

- Workspace `AGENTS.md` and `.cursor/rules/` (auto-loaded)
- User rules from Cursor settings (auto-loaded)
- The codebase via Read / Glob / SemanticSearch
- Git history via `git log`

Include in a handoff prompt only what is NOT discoverable from the
above:

- Path to the authoritative spec (plan file, ticket, design doc)
- Which phase / task / scope to start
- Decisions made in chat but not yet in the spec (branch strategy,
  acceptance changes, side-quest learnings worth carrying forward)

If a draft handoff prompt is summarizing the tech stack, recent commits,
file locations, conventions, or restating workspace rules: delete those
sections. The agent will discover or already-have them. Restating them
just risks drift and burns tokens.

## Good

```
Read <path-to-plan>.md in full, then start Phase N — <title>. Switch to
agent mode and follow the Runbook. Update todos as you go.

Notes from the previous session: <one or two bullets of decisions or
side-quests that aren't in the plan>.
```

## Bad

A 100-line prompt that re-summarizes the tech stack, recent commits,
and coding conventions before getting to the actual task.
